The City and SWWC have implemented safety precautions to prevent and mitigate a chlorine release.  These include maintenance, training, and inspection procedures, as well as an Emergency Action Plan. 

City management and SWWC are committed to:
-Preventing accidents;
-Training employees in correct response procedures in the event of an accident;
-Providing leadership to the community with respect to emergency preparedness;
-Addressing any citizen concerns by fully explaining potential hazards associated with facility operations and all steps being taken to prevent and mitigate accidents; and
-Being a good corporate citizen of Fort Bend County.

With these objectives in mind, this Risk Management Plan provides information about the City's management of the risks associated with the chlorine disinfection process, but more importantly stresses the commitment to ensuring a safe operation for employees, visitors, and community.
